       The value of CLK_TCK may be variable and it should not  be
       assumed  that  CLK_TCK  is  a  compile-time constant.  The
       value  of  CLK_TCK  is  the   same   as   the   value   of
       sysconf(_SC_CLK_TCK).

       sysconf can also return the following values:
       ---------------------------------------------------------------
       Name                   Return value
       ---------------------------------------------------------------
       _SC_ATEXIT_MAX         Maximum number of atexit functions that
                              can be registered
       _SC_NPROCESSORS_CONF   Number of configured processors
       _SC_NPROCESSORS_ONLN   Number of online processors
       _SC_NPROCESSES         Number of processes per real user id
       _SC_PAGE_SIZE          Size in bytes of physical page
       _SC_PAGESIZE           Size in bytes of physical page
       _SC_SYSTEM_ID          Persistent, system-generated identifier

   EErrrroorrss
       If name is an invalid value, sysconf will  return  -1  and
       set  errno  to EINVAL.  If sysconf fails due to a value of
       name that is not defined on the system, the function  will
       return  a value of -1 without changing the value of errno.

